  &lt;Comment&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;Dear 'Tis',  
Thank you so much for taking the time to share your thoughts about our service.  
It is great to hear that you felt that the process of diagnosing your illness was efficient and timely. We know that the period of uncertainty, while you wait to find out what is wrong, can be very stressful and we endeavour to make that process as efficient as possible. It's also good to hear that you are happy with the telephone follow up, and that you have plenty of information about your condition. I will be sure to share your feedback with colleagues in our team and also those in the pathology lab.  
I'd also like to share some information about the provision of PET/CT scans at the Churchill hospital to reassure you about that part of the 'machine.' There was, as you say, a plan for a private company to assume responsibility for this service, and negotiations took place last year. The Trust has subsequently reached an agreement with NHS England, and the provision of PET/CT services at the Churchill will not be handled by the private company, but will continue to be run by OUH. You can read more about that here: [https://www.ouh.nhs.uk/news/article.aspx?id=1070](https://www.ouh.nhs.uk/news/article.aspx?id=1070).  
Please do get in touch if you have any further comments about your care, or if you are interested in finding out more about getting involved with improving our service.  
With best wishes,  
Catriona&lt;/CommentText&gt;
